{
  "stem": "10162.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 50.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I just could not resist, you know, when it was just going to be almost sort of in-- in the delicious, malleable texture or-- or-- or feeling.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I just would have to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I know-- knew it was a crime and a sin, but I just had to make something out of it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And miraculously, it wound up in my mother's vitrine, what they called.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So as much as she scorned, but it-- at it, she still displayed it with pride.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because when it was thin and it-- and it-- it cooled off, it looked like a-- a fine porcelain.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And also, the Hungarian bread when we were-- we always had bread on the table at meals-- is kind of a glutinous texture also that you can-- you can-- instead of eating it, you can manipulate it under the table and make little heads, and dogs, and animals out of it.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I always did something like that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Once I was ill and I was doing my thing, maybe with plasticine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then this doctor who used to come to the house said, you do that?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I cannot believe that she made that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's how it just sort of worked out that they decided that they should-- they should give me private lessons.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no such thing as sculptor in Debrecen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, there were two very well-known painters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I became their student.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I stuck with painting for many years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I actually went back to my original love of sculpture when I came to this country, in stone and wood.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Drastically changing, right?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- well, when World War II was progressing and the anti-Semitic propaganda was-- first of all, Hungary became an ally of Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And slowly, one by one, less and less people who used to greet you friendly on the street would greet you less friendly, and eventually not at all.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I would hear this at home, the talk between my parents and their friends.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And actually, in Hungary, all this happened much faster.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everything was very condensed in time compared to what happened in-- in Poland and Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We-- we really didn't feel anti-Semitism until '43.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then in '44, suddenly, it just-- the world fell apart you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had to-- well, even before we had to wear the yellow star, suddenly, there were stores having a sign out saying [HUNGARIAN], which means Hungarian store or Hungarian business, which really meant that Jews are not welcome, this is a Hungarian store.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So suddenly there was-- were Hungarians and Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And suddenly, they say Hungarian store.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this store might have been a toy store where we were going ever since I remembered and they-- they greeted my-- my mother very-- very politely.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we couldn't go in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this was just all around us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My-- my mother had two cousins, girls, who were about the same ages she was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were also living in Debrecen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then they also got married.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So her two cousins were her best friends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And their husbands were best friends with my father.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were also always some friends coming in from-- you know, from other families.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But this-- the three girls were very close.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And actually, my mother cousin's son, who was also an only child and also about the same age as I am, was my best friend.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were brought up together.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my father had a sister, an older sister, who lived in Debrecen who we were friendly like family.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But she was older than my mother and not quite-- it wasn't-- it wasn't real friendship, just family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I only had one grandmother living in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because my grandfather, who I remember-- he must have been maybe-- I must have been maybe seven when he died.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's mother, right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father's parents died when I was maybe a year old or earlier.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I don't remember them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I just-- I-- my mother went fairly regularly because she had a younger brother in France.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she would go visit him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she went once or twice.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know they went to Vienna.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then she used to go to-- to Italy on a tour to Abbazia, it was called.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now I think it's Opatija.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's part of whatever that is.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It's not Yugoslavia anymore.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I-- I don't know if it's Serbia or Croatia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the only time I went with my mother was to Italy, to this Abbazia once.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I must have been six.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So I have very, very little recollection.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were discussions, because this was the discussion of the day among Jews altogether.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And everybody came and loved to hear my father's opinion.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
